TextBody:
ref:_00D7091pB._500Q000OMK2H:ref

Dear Daniel,

Here what I've done to troubleshoot
I go to Device Control -> Global Settings -> DPI Configuration and make sure "Bypass on HTTP Errors Indicating mTLS Requirements" is active.
Then I go to Denylist and Allowlist -> Allowlists -> Deep Packet Inspection tab
I add apps.pertamina.com and *.pertamina.com in "Default DPI Bypass List"
[cid:image001.png@01DBB4F7.94B5DD30]

I go to the client to update the agent by right click on the icon located in system tray -> Update Policies Now
Close all browser, wait couple of seconds, open browser and open https://apps.pertamina.com/ivendor
Capctha still not appear.
[cid:image002.png@01DBB4F7.94B5DD30]
I uninstall EPP in affected client, close all browser, open browser and open https://apps.pertamina.com/ivendor
Capctha appear.
[cid:image003.png@01DBB4F7.94B5DD30]

The issue is start yesterday. It is the 1st time the user attempting to access https://apps.pertamina.com/ivendor

Client: Windows 11 24H2, agent version: 6.2.3.1010
Server: EPP hosted, version: 5.9.4.1

I think the client log is gone with the client uninstallation. Can I gather the log from the server?

Regards,

Hi Robby,

My colleague Daniel is out of office today but I would like to help with this ticket.
As I can see the client 6.2.4.2 is not available in your appliance, I am providing you an offline patch that will inject that version of the client in the server:
http://download.endpointprotector.com/offline_agent_patches/MP-HWA-EPP4-U0066-M0001.tar.gz

The offline patch needs to be uploaded under Live Update menu  > Offline Patch  - choose the file downloaded from the link above without extracting the arvhive.
Wait 10 minutes then refresh the entire page - the new client should be available under System Configuration menu.


Best regards,
